==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penduline
<hw>Pen"du`line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Pendulum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A European titmouse
(<spn>Parus pendulinus</spn>, syn. <spn>Aegithalus pendulinus</spn>). It
is noted for its elegant pendulous purselike nest, made of the down of
willow trees and lined with feathers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pendulosity</ent>⟦br⟧
